    <note>Li(2) Kuan [1048] He was a member of a branch of the Longxi jun Li(2). His 8th generation ancestor, Chang(2) [12309], moved from Longxi to Guangzhou, Guangshan county in Tang (fl. 820). Kuan's sixth generation ancestor, Ying(4) [12310],  followed Wang(2) Chao [3937] to Fujian and settled in Jianning, Jianan xian. His grandfather, Yin [3548], served in the administration of Southern Tang, and moved the family to Hongzhou, Nanchang xian. Xuzhou's [3505] son, Xuji's [3504] nephew, Zhang(1) Tingjie's [7014] father-in-law, and Yan(5) Shu's [2073] wife's cousin. Xuzhou's father-in-law was Zhao(1) Xiang [360]. Kuan was buried in Hongzhou, Xinjian county. However, Fujian TZ, 147.2b records Xuji as a Jianan jinshi in 977 and Fujian TZ, 150.39a lists both Xuzhou and Kuan as Jianan residents who entered via yin. I take burial place of Kuan as definitive and Fujian TZ as anachronistic. Guangxi TZ, 21.15b; SS, 300.23a; Wang Anshi,  WJ, 88.916, 97.1002-1004; Yu Jing, WJ, 19.13b-18a; 18a-20a. CBD, 2, 905.</note>
